The paper deals with entity resolution in knowledge bases, which is a common problem in databases (cs.DB). The approach proposed in the paper involves leveraging human input and probabilistic inference, which are techniques commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the use of crowdsourcing and human-computer interaction, which are relevant to the sub-categories of social and information sciences (cs.SI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
